_refine.details                                  
;ELECTRON DENSITY FAILS TO RESOLVE THE POSITIONS OF SOME LIGAND ATOMS. TRUNCATION OF THE LIGAND MODEL RESULTS IN AN APPARENT SYMMETRY THAT CANNOT BE RESOLVED BY THE ELECTRON DENSITY ALONE. OUR CHOSEN LIGAND POSE IS SUPPORTED BY PRECEDENT FROM PDB ENTRIES 4IFG AND 4WJC. MOREOVER, OUR POSE ESTABLISHES ADDITIONAL HYDROGEN BONDS WHEN COMPARED TO THE MOST PLAUSIBLE ALTERNATIVE POSE.
;
